Other antibiotics (thiostrepton) block the 50S subunit from interacting with elongation factors G and Tu (EF-G, Ef-Tu), preventing GTP-dependent reactions of peptidyl transferase, and translocation, respectively. Other antibiotics (macrolides) prevent protein translocation.

cvterm.name: fosmidomycin
cvterm.definition: Fosmidomycin is an inhibitor of 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase, an enzyme in the non-mevalonate pathway for isoprenoid synthesis. It is active against enterobacteria, but not against Gram-positive bacteria or anaerobes.

cvterm.name: fusidic acid
cvterm.definition: Fusidic acid is the only commercially available fusidane, a group steroid like antibiotics. It is most active against Gram-positive bacteria, and acts by inhibiting elongation factor G to block protein synthesis.

cvterm.name: cycloserine
cvterm.definition: Cycloserine is an anti-mycobacterial agent, and is active against enterobacteria, streptococci, M. tuberculosis, Staphylococcus aureus, and many Gram-negative and Gram-positive bacteria. It inhibits cell wall biosynthesis.

cvterm.name: mecillinam
cvterm.definition: Mecillinam is a broad-spectrum beta-lactam antibiotic that was semi-synthetically derived to have a different drug centre, being a 6-alpha-amidinopenicillanate instead of a 6-alpha-acylaminopenicillanate. Contrasting most beta-lactam drugs, mecillinam is most active against Gram-negative bacteria. It binds specifically to penicillin binding protein 2 (PBP2).

cvterm.name: pefloxacin
cvterm.definition: Pefloxacin is structurally and functionally similar to norfloxacin. It is poorly active against mycobacteria, while anaerobes are resistant.

cvterm.name: ethambutol sensitive embC
cvterm.definition: EmbC is an arabinosyltransferase involved in lipoarabinomannan synthesis.

cvterm.name: ethambutol sensitive embA
cvterm.definition: EmbA is an arabinosyltransferase that works as a heterodimer with EmbB. It is involved in the synthesis of arabinogalactan, a component of the mycobacterial cell wall.

cvterm.name: ethambutol sensitive embB
cvterm.definition: EmbB is an arabinosyltransferase that works as a heterodimer with EmbA. It is involved in the synthesis of arabinogalactan, a component of the mycobacterial cell wall.

cvterm.name: antibiotic sensitive topoisomerase subunit
cvterm.definition: Topoisomerases are responsible for winding and relaxing supercoiled DNA. The subunits of gyrase (gyrA, gyrB) and topoisomerase IV (parC, parE, parY) are targeted by antibiotics.

cvterm.name: avoparcin
cvterm.definition: Avoparcin is a glycopeptide antibiotic that is an analog of vancomycin. It was formally used to treat animals, but has since been banned because of its selection for vancomycin-resistant enterococci.

cvterm.name: AbeS
cvterm.definition: AbeS in an efflux pump of the SMR family of transporters found in Acinetobacter baumannii.

cvterm.name: PatA-PatB
cvterm.definition: PatA-PatB is an efflux protein complex that is associated with fluoroquinolone resistance in Streptococcus pneumoniae. Experiments indicate that PatA and PatB form a heterodimeric transporter.

cvterm.name: AdeABC
cvterm.definition: AdeABC is an RND multidrug efflux system in Acinetobacter species, notably A. baunmannii. AdeA is a membrane fusion protein, AdeB is the inner membrane transporter, and AdeC is the outer membrane factor. It confers resistance to tigecycline.

cvterm.name: AdeFGH
cvterm.definition: AdeFGH is a RND multidrug efflux pump expressed in Acinetobacter baumannii. It confers resistance to fluoroquinolone, tetracycline, tigecycline, chloramphenicol, clindamycin, trimethoprim, and sulfamethoxazole.

cvterm.name: AdeIJK
cvterm.definition: AdeIJK is a RND multidrug efflux pump expressed in Acinetobacter baumannii. It confers resistance to beta-lactams, chloramphenicol, tetracycline, erythromycin, lincosamides, fluoroquinolone, fusidic acid, novobiocin, rifampicin, trimethoprim, acridine, pyronine, and safranin.

cvterm.name: CmeABC
cvterm.definition: CmeABC is a multidrug efflux pump in Campylobacter jejuni. Its overexpression led to enhanced resistance to ciprofloxacin, norfloxacin, cefotaxime, fusidic acid, and erythromycin. CmeA acts as the periplasmic fusion protein, CmeB is the inner membrane transporter, and CmeC is an outer membrane protein.

cvterm.name: adeA
cvterm.definition: AdeA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex AdeABC.

cvterm.name: adeB
cvterm.definition: AdeB is the multidrug transporter of the adeABC efflux system.

cvterm.name: adeC
cvterm.definition: AdeC is the outer membrane factor of the AdeABC multidrug efflux complex. It can be replaced by other outer membrane channels, and is not essential for antibiotic resistance.

cvterm.name: adeF
cvterm.definition: AdeF is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex AdeFGH.

cvterm.name: adeG
cvterm.definition: AdeG is the inner membrane transporter of the AdeFGH multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: adeH
cvterm.definition: AdeH is the outer membrane channel protein of the AdeFGH multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: adeI
cvterm.definition: AdeI is the membrane fusion protein of the AdeIJK multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: adeJ
cvterm.definition: AdeJ is a RND efflux protein that acts as the inner membrane transporter of the AdeIJK efflux complex. It has 57% identity with E. coli AcrB.

cvterm.name: adeK
cvterm.definition: AdeK is the outer membrane factor protein in the adeIJK multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: cmeA
cvterm.definition: CmeA is the membrane fusion protein of the CmeABC multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: cmeB
cvterm.definition: CmeB is the inner membrane transporter the CmeABC multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: cmeC
cvterm.definition: CmeC is the outer membrane channel protein of the CmeABC multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: MdsABC
cvterm.definition: MdsABC, or GesABC, is a RND-type efflux complex found in Salmonella. In addition to its metal-efflux system, GesABC is also capable of exporting beta-lactams, chloramphenicol, and thiamphenicol. GesB is the inner membrane transporter and is similar to MexF; GesA is the membrane-fusion protein, and GesC is the outer membrane factor.

cvterm.name: MdtABC-TolC
cvterm.definition: MdtABC-TolC is a multidrug efflux system in Gram-negative bacteria, including E. coli and Salmonella. MdtA is a membrane fusion protein; TolC is the outer membrane channel; MdtBC form a drug transporter. In the absence of MdtB, the MdtAC-TolC has narrower drug specificity, leading to the loss of novobiocin resistance, for example.

cvterm.name: MdtEF-TolC
cvterm.definition: MdtEF-TolC is a multidrug efflux complex in Gram-negative bacteria, including E. coli. MdtE is the membrane fusion protein, MdtF is the inner membrane transporter, while TolC is the outer membrane channel.

cvterm.name: mdsA
cvterm.definition: MdsA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug and metal efflux complex MdsABC.

cvterm.name: mdsB
cvterm.definition: MdsB is the inner membrane transporter of the multidrug and metal efflux complex MdsABC.

cvterm.name: mdsC
cvterm.definition: MdsC is the outer membrane channel of the multidrug and metal efflux complex MdsABC.

cvterm.name: mdtA
cvterm.definition: MdtA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex mdtABC.

cvterm.name: mdtB
cvterm.definition: MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mdtC
cvterm.definition: MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB, MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity.

cvterm.name: mdtE
cvterm.definition: MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.

cvterm.name: mdtF
cvterm.definition: MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.

cvterm.name: MexCD-OprJ
cvterm.definition: MexCD-OprJ is a multidrug efflux protein expressed in the Gram-negative Pseudomonas aeruginosa. MexC is the membrane fusion protein; MexD is the inner membrane transporter; and OprJ is the outer membrane channel. MexAB-OprM is associated with resistance to fluoroquinolones, chloramphenicol, and macrolides.

cvterm.name: MexEF-OprN
cvterm.definition: MexEF-OprN is a multidrug efflux protein expressed in the Gram-negative Pseudomonas aeruginosa. MexE is the membrane fusion protein; MexF is the inner membrane transporter; and OprN is the outer membrane channel. MexEF-OprN is associated with resistance to fluoroquinolones, chloramphenicol, and trimethoprim.

cvterm.name: MexGHI-OpmD
cvterm.definition: MexGHI-OpmD is an efflux complex expressed in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. MexG is a membrane protein required for drug export; MexH is the membrane fusion protein; MexI is the inner membrane transporter; and MexJ is the outer membrane channel protein. MexGHI-OpmD confers resistance to vanadium, norfloxacin, and acriflavin.

cvterm.name: mexC
cvterm.definition: MexC is the membrane fusion protein of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mexD
cvterm.definition: MexD is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexCD-OprJ complex.

cvterm.name: oprJ
cvterm.definition: OprJ is the outer membrane channel component of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mexE
cvterm.definition: MexE is the membrane fusion protein of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mexF
cvterm.definition: MexF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexEF-OprN complex.

cvterm.name: oprN
cvterm.definition: OprN is the outer membrane channel component of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mexG
cvterm.definition: MexG is a membrane protein required for MexGHI-OpmD efflux activity.

cvterm.name: mexH
cvterm.definition: MexH is the membrane fusion protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.

cvterm.name: mexI
cvterm.definition: MexI is the inner membrane transporter of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.

cvterm.name: ompD
cvterm.definition: OpmD is the outer membrane channel protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.

cvterm.name: mtrC
cvterm.definition: MtrC is the membrane fusion protein of the MtrCDE multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mtrD
cvterm.definition: MtrD is the inner membrane multidrug transporter of the MtrCDE efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mtrE
cvterm.definition: MtrE is an outer membrane exporter protein that is part of the MtrCDE multidrug efflux complex.

cvterm.name: mexS
cvterm.definition: MexS is a suppressor of MexT, which is an activator of the multidrug pump MexEF-OprN. Mutations in MexS lead to multidrug resistance.

cvterm.name: mexT
cvterm.definition: MexT is a LysR-type transcriptional activator that positively regulates the expression of MexEF-OprN and OprD.

cvterm.name: mgrA
cvterm.definition: MgrA, also known as NorR, is a regulator for norA, norB, and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression, but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.

cvterm.name: mtrA
cvterm.definition: MtrA is a transcriptional activator of the MtrCDE multidrug efflux pump of Neisseria gonorrhoeae.

cvterm.name: mtrR
cvterm.definition: MtrR is a repressor of mtrCDE expression. Mutations in mtrR increase multidrug resistance.

cvterm.name: nalC
cvterm.definition: NalC is a repressor of PA3720-PA3719, which are positive regulators of MexAB-OprM. Thus, nalC mutants confer multidrug resistance.

cvterm.name: nalD
cvterm.definition: NalD is a repressor of MexAB-OprM. Mutations lead to multidrug resistance and MexAB-OprM overexpression.

cvterm.name: nfxB
cvterm.definition: NfxB is a repressor of the efflux pump mexCD-oprJ and itself.

cvterm.name: phoPQ
cvterm.definition: PhoPQ is a two-component regulatory system that controls Salmonella virulence. It regulates MacAB-TolC expression and is itself activated by low Mg2+ concentrations.

cvterm.name: pmrA
cvterm.definition: PmrA is a MFS-type efflux pump expressed in Streptococcus pneumoniae that confers low-level resistance to norfloxacin, ciprofloxacin, and acriflavine.

cvterm.name: ramA
cvterm.definition: RamA ("resistance antibiotic multiple

cvterm.name: ramR
cvterm.definition: RamR is a repressor that regulates RamA expression. Mutations lead to the upregulation of AcrAB, which is positively regulated by RamA.

cvterm.name: rob
cvterm.definition: Rob is a positive regulator for the acrAB efflux genes, and is structurally similar to SoxS and MarA.

cvterm.name: sdiA
cvterm.definition: SdiA is cell division regulator that is also a positive regulator of AcrAB.

cvterm.name: soxRS
cvterm.definition: SoxRS is a two-component regulator part of the superoxide stress response. It is a positive regulator for many multidrug efflux pumps.

cvterm.name: baeR
cvterm.definition: BaeR is a response regulator that promotes the expression of MdtABC and AcrD efflux complexes.

cvterm.name: baeS
cvterm.definition: BaeS is a sensor kinase in the BaeSR regulatory system. While it phosphorylates BaeR to increase its activity, BaeS is not necessary for overexpressed BaeR to confer resistance.

cvterm.name: cpxA
cvterm.definition: CpxA is a membrane-localized sensor kinase that is activated by envelope stress. It starts a kinase cascade that activates CpxR, which promotes efflux complex expression.

cvterm.name: cpxR
cvterm.definition: CpxR is a regulator that promotes acrD expression when phosphorylated by a cascade involving CpxA, a sensor kinase.

cvterm.name: evgA
cvterm.definition: EvgA, when phosphorylated, is a positive regulator for efflux protein complexes emrKY and mdtEF. While usually phosphorylated in a EvgS dependent manner, it can be phosphorylated in the absence of EvgS when overexpressed.

cvterm.name: evgS
cvterm.definition: EvgS is a sensor protein that phosphorylates the regulatory protein EvgA.

cvterm.name: phoP
cvterm.definition: PhoP is a direct repressor of the macAB efflux genes.

cvterm.name: phoQ
cvterm.definition: PhoQ is a sensor protein that is induced by low Mg2+ concentrations. When activated, PhoQ donates a phosphate to activate PhoP.

cvterm.name: soxR
cvterm.definition: SoxR, in E. coli and Salmonella, is a sensory protein that upregulates soxS expression in the presence of redox-cycling drugs. This stress response leads to the expression many multidrug efflux pumps. In Pseudomonas aeruginosa, which lacks SoxS, SoxR is able to directly upregulate the expression of the MexGHI-OpmD efflux pump.

cvterm.name: soxS
cvterm.definition: SoxS is a global regulator that up-regulates the expression of AcrAB efflux genes. It also reduces OmpF expression to decrease cell membrane permeability.

cvterm.name: arlR
cvterm.definition: ArlR is a response regulator that binds to the norA promoter to activate expression. ArlR must first be phosphorylated by ArlS.

cvterm.name: arlS
cvterm.definition: ArlS is a protein histidine kinase that phosphorylates ArlR, a promoter for norA expression.

cvterm.name: 16S ribosomal RNA methyltransferase
cvterm.definition: Methyltransferases that modify the 16S rRNA of the 30S subunit of bacterial ribosomes, conferring resistance to drugs that target 16S rRNA.

cvterm.name: armA
cvterm.definition: ArmA is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase that targets mature or nearly mature 30S subunits. It transfers a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to N7-G1405 of the 16S rRNA, an aminoglycoside binding site.

cvterm.name: rmtA
cvterm.definition: RmtA is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa which methylates G1405 of the 16S rRNA. It confers high level resistance to many aminoglycosides.

cvterm.name: rmtB
cvterm.definition: RmtB is a 16S rRNA methyltransferase that targets mature or nearly mature 30S subunits. It transfers a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to N7-G1405 of the 16S rRNA, an aminoglycoside binding site.

cvterm.name: rmtC
cvterm.definition: RmtC is a rRNA methyltransferase found in Proteus mirabilis with high level resistance to similar to aminoglycosides, with the exception of non-4,6-disubstituted deoxystreptamines (streptomycin and neomycin). It has also been isolated in Salmonella enterica ser. Virchow. It is hypothesized to methylate G1405, like related methyltransferases RmtA, RmtB, and ArmA.

cvterm.name: sgm
cvterm.definition: Sgm, or sisomicin-gentamicin methyltransferase, methylates G1405 of 15S rRNA to confer resistance to various aminoglycosides.

cvterm.name: mprF
cvterm.definition: MprF is a integral membrane protein that modifies the negatively-charged phosphatidylglycerol on the membrane surface of both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria. This confers resistance to cationic peptides that disrupt the cell membrane, including defensins.

cvterm.name: fluoroquinolone resistant gyrB
cvterm.definition: Point mutations in DNA gyrase subunit B (gyrB) observed in Mycobacterium tuberculosis can result in resistance to fluoroquinolones.

cvterm.name: oleD
cvterm.definition: OleD is a glycotransferase found in Streptomyces antibioticus, a natural producer of oleandomycin. OleD can glycosylate a wide range of macrolides.

cvterm.name: oleI
cvterm.definition: OleI is a glycosyltransferase found in Streptomyces antibioticus, a natural producer of oleandomycin. OleI glycosylates oleandomycin to confer self-resistance.

cvterm.name: oleandomycin
cvterm.definition: Oleandomycin is a 14-membered macrolide produced by Streptomyces antibioticus. It is ssimilar to erythromycin, and contains a desosamine amino sugar and an oleandrose sugar. It targets the 50S ribosomal subunit to prevent protein synthesis.

cvterm.name: streptothricin resistance gene
cvterm.definition: Genes conferring resistance to streptothricins.

cvterm.name: streptothricin acetyltransferase (sat)
cvterm.definition: AcetylCoA dependent acetyltransferase that acetylate streptothricins such as nourseothricin at position 16 (beta position of beta-lysine).

cvterm.name: triclosan
cvterm.definition: Triclosan is a common antibacterial agent added to many consumer products as a biocide. It is an inhibitor of fatty acid biosynthesis by blocking enoyl-carrier protein reductase (FabI).

cvterm.name: fatty acid synthesis enzyme targeted by antibiotic
cvterm.definition: Antibiotics can target bacteria-specific fatty acid biosynthesis enzymes.

cvterm.name: fabI
cvterm.definition: FabI is an enoyl reductase enzyme that synthesizes type II fatty acids.
